  "market_context": "BTCUSDT was in a downtrend on the daily chart; a hammer candle formed after a decline, followed by a strong upward move. The analyst highlighted this as a successful reversal signal.",
  "key_observation": "A hammer candle was automatically identified by the 'All Candlestick Patterns' indicator on the BTCUSDT daily chart, and price reversed strongly to the upside afterward.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst opened the 'All Candlestick Patterns' indicator on TradingView and configured it to detect only hammer patterns using SMA 50 trend filtering.",
    "Step 2: He switched to the daily timeframe to examine historical hammer occurrences on BTCUSDT.",
    "Step 3: He pointed out a specific hammer candle that appeared after a downtrend, noting the long lower wick and small body characteristic of the pattern.",
    "Step 4: He observed that immediately after the hammer, price made a strong move upward, confirming the reversal signal."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reversed strongly to the upside after the hammer, resulting in a successful bullish signal.",
  "lessons": "Hammer patterns—especially when confirmed by subsequent strong momentum and filtered by trend (e.g., SMA 50)—can provide reliable reversal signals on higher timeframes like daily charts, though not all hammers succeed.",
